(
<figureCitation id="132F2A6BC963FFD47E9BFEA41EAC11E4" box="[159,229,380,406]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="29.[151,255,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,362,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-111@29.[153,1438,349,1850]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 9. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Bathyditrupa hovei, ZMA V.Pol.5325. A—collar chaetae, B—fourth bundle of thoracic chaetae, C—anterior abdominal chaeta, D—third row of thoracic uncini, E—gouged pegs of posterior thoracic uncini from below, F—first row of abdominal uncini." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB36EEC963FFD47E93FE111CAA1192" blockId="28.[151,739,457,512]" box="[151,739,457,481]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC963FFD47E93FE111F6F1193" bold="true" box="[151,294,457,481]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Type-species</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC963FFD47F30FE111CAA1192" authority="Kupriyanova, 1993 b" authorityName="Kupriyanova" authorityYear="1993" box="[308,739,457,480]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Bathyditrupa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hovei">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC963FFD47F30FE111C481192" box="[308,513,457,480]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Bathyditrupa hovei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF854B1FC963FFD47C0CFE111CAA1192" author="Kupriyanova, E. K." box="[520,739,457,480]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="21 - 28" refId="ref62782" refString="Kupriyanova, E. K. (1993 b) Deep-water Serpulidae (Annelida, Polychaeta) from the Kurile-Kamchatka trench: 2. Genera Bathyditrupa, Bathyvermilia and Protis. Zoologichesky Zhurnal, 72, 21 - 28." type="journal article" year="1993">Kupriyanova, 1993b</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB36EEC963FFD47E93FE311F331272" blockId="28.[151,739,457,512]" box="[151,378,489,512]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Number of species: 1</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB36EEC963FFD47E93FDF11EA01461" blockId="28.[151,1436,553,1314]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Tube free, curved but not coiled, white, opaque, rectangular in cross-section; collar-like rings absent. Granular overlay absent. Operculum inverse conical, with brown chitinous endplate, flat or slightly concave. Opercular ampulla gradually merges (constriction absent) into thick, rather triangular peduncle with pinnules, but without wings. Peduncle inserted as the second dorsal radiole on one side. Pseudoperculum absent. Arrangement of radioles semi-circular, up to 6 per lobe. Branchial eyes not observed. Inter-radiolar membrane and stylodes absent. Mouth palps not observed. 5 thoracic chaetigerous segments. Collar non-lobed, short, with entire edge. Tonguelets absent. Thoracic membranes short, ending at second thoracic segment. Collar chaetae limbate (
<figureCitation id="132F2A6BC963FFD47F59FCE01FF21320" box="[349,443,824,850]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="29.[151,255,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,362,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-111@29.[153,1438,349,1850]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 9. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Bathyditrupa hovei, ZMA V.Pol.5325. A—collar chaetae, B—fourth bundle of thoracic chaetae, C—anterior abdominal chaeta, D—third row of thoracic uncini, E—gouged pegs of posterior thoracic uncini from below, F—first row of abdominal uncini." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC963FFD47FCBFCE01C0D1323" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[463,580,824,849]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC963FFD47FCBFCE01C0D1323" box="[463,580,824,849]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Apomatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
chaetae absent (
<figureCitation id="132F2A6BC963FFD47D00FCE01D281320" box="[772,865,824,850]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="29.[151,255,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,362,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-111@29.[153,1438,349,1850]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 9. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Bathyditrupa hovei, ZMA V.Pol.5325. A—collar chaetae, B—fourth bundle of thoracic chaetae, C—anterior abdominal chaeta, D—third row of thoracic uncini, E—gouged pegs of posterior thoracic uncini from below, F—first row of abdominal uncini." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
). Thoracic uncini saw-to-rasp-shaped, with up to 4 (?6) teeth in a row above peg, with about 15 curved teeth in a row in profile (
<figureCitation id="132F2A6BC963FFD47A23FC861ACC130A" box="[1063,1157,862,888]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="29.[151,255,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,362,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-111@29.[153,1438,349,1850]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 9. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Bathyditrupa hovei, ZMA V.Pol.5325. A—collar chaetae, B—fourth bundle of thoracic chaetae, C—anterior abdominal chaeta, D—third row of thoracic uncini, E—gouged pegs of posterior thoracic uncini from below, F—first row of abdominal uncini." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
). Anterior peg bifurcate in high-power microscopy, but clearly gouged when studied by SEM (
<figureCitation id="132F2A6BC963FFD47DCCFC5D1A6A13ED" box="[968,1059,901,927]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="29.[151,255,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,362,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-111@29.[153,1438,349,1850]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 9. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Bathyditrupa hovei, ZMA V.Pol.5325. A—collar chaetae, B—fourth bundle of thoracic chaetae, C—anterior abdominal chaeta, D—third row of thoracic uncini, E—gouged pegs of posterior thoracic uncini from below, F—first row of abdominal uncini." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
). Thoracic triangular depression absent. Abdominal chaetae all capillary (
<figureCitation id="132F2A6BC963FFD47C8AFC741CB913B4" box="[654,752,940,966]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="29.[151,255,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,362,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-111@29.[153,1438,349,1850]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 9. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Bathyditrupa hovei, ZMA V.Pol.5325. A—collar chaetae, B—fourth bundle of thoracic chaetae, C—anterior abdominal chaeta, D—third row of thoracic uncini, E—gouged pegs of posterior thoracic uncini from below, F—first row of abdominal uncini." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
), posterior ones slightly longer; abdominal uncini raspshaped (
<figureCitation id="132F2A6BC963FFD47EFCFC0A1F1B139E" box="[248,338,978,1004]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="29.[151,255,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,362,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-111@29.[153,1438,349,1850]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 9. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Bathyditrupa hovei, ZMA V.Pol.5325. A—collar chaetae, B—fourth bundle of thoracic chaetae, C—anterior abdominal chaeta, D—third row of thoracic uncini, E—gouged pegs of posterior thoracic uncini from below, F—first row of abdominal uncini." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 9F</figureCitation>
). Achaetous anterior abdominal zone short, just one or two segments. Posterior glandular pad absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30E6565C963FFD47EC2FBC71B76151D" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAB36EEC963FFD47EC2FBC71FE81550" blockId="28.[151,1436,553,1314]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC963FFD47EC2FBC71F71144B" bold="true" box="[198,312,1055,1081]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks</emphasis>
. This abyssal species had only been reported from the Kurile-Kamchatka trench (
<bibRefCitation id="EF854B1FC963FFD47B05FBF81EAC1412" author="Kupriyanova, E. K." pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="21 - 28" refId="ref62782" refString="Kupriyanova, E. K. (1993 b) Deep-water Serpulidae (Annelida, Polychaeta) from the Kurile-Kamchatka trench: 2. Genera Bathyditrupa, Bathyvermilia and Protis. Zoologichesky Zhurnal, 72, 21 - 28." type="journal article" year="1993">Kupriyanova 1993b</bibRefCitation>
). We studied 2 additional specimens from the North Pacific Ocean, collected by the R/V 
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC963FFD47B1CFB9F1B2F1412" box="[1304,1382,1095,1120]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Vityaz,</emphasis>
Sta. 3151, near the Emperor Seamounts, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE205029C963FFD47C42FBB51C8114F5" box="[582,712,1133,1159]" degrees="44" direction="north" minutes="28" orientation="latitude" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" precision="15" seconds="3" value="44.4675">44°28'3'' N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE205029C963FFD47CD5FBB51D1114F5" box="[721,856,1133,1159]" degrees="170" direction="east" minutes="07" orientation="longitude" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" precision="15" seconds="0" value="170.11667">170°07'0''E</geoCoordinate>
, grab, 
<quantity id="4CEC9B0BC963FFD47DADFBB51A4C14F5" box="[937,1029,1133,1159]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.237" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="m" value="5237.0">5237 m</quantity>
, ZMA V.Pol. 5326; Sta. 4370, NE off 
<collectingRegion id="49D0F80CC963FFD47EBBFB4C1F5E14DC" box="[191,279,1172,1198]" country="United States of America" name="Hawaii" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Hawaii</collectingRegion>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE205029C963FFD47F27FB4C1FEF14DC" box="[291,422,1172,1198]" degrees="26" direction="north" minutes="04" orientation="latitude" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" precision="15" seconds="2" value="26.067223">26°04'2'' N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE205029C963FFD47FB6FB4C1C0014DC" box="[434,585,1172,1198]" degrees="153" direction="west" minutes="49" orientation="longitude" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" precision="15" seconds="3" value="-153.8175">153°49'3'' W</geoCoordinate>
, grab, 
<quantity id="4CEC9B0BC963FFD47C93FB4C1CB814DC" box="[663,753,1172,1198]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.05" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="m" value="6050.0">6050 m</quantity>
, ZMA V.Pol. 5325. The characteristic feature of the genus is a free, unattached tube similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC963FFD47CA8FB631D4014A6" authorityName="Berkeley" authorityYear="1835" box="[684,777,1211,1236]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Ditrupa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC963FFD47CA8FB631D4014A6" box="[684,777,1211,1236]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ditrupa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but rectangular in cross-section and without an outer hyaline layer (see 
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC963FFD47F7FFB381FA61488" bold="true" box="[379,495,1248,1274]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">The tube</emphasis>
, p. 7). It is probably synonymous with 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC963FFD47DE7FB391B2C1489" authority="Jager (2004: 140)" authorityName="Jager" authorityPageNumber="140" authorityYear="2004" box="[995,1381,1249,1275]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Nogrobs" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fide">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC963FFD47DE7FB391A361488" box="[995,1151,1249,1274]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Nogrobs fide</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF854B1FC963FFD47A8FFB391B2C1489" author="Jager, M." box="[1163,1381,1249,1275]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="121 - 249" refId="ref62313" refString="Jager, M. (2004) Serpulidae und Spirorbidae (Polychaeta sedentaria) aus Campan und Maastricht von Norddeutschland, den Niederlanden, Belgien und angrenzenden Gebieten. Geologisches Jahrbuch, A 157, 121 - 249." type="journal article" year="2004">Jäger (2004: 140)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, see remarks below (p. 69).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB36EEC963FFD47E93FA8D1B76151D" blockId="28.[151,1343,1365,1391]" box="[151,1343,1365,1391]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="4C144D6DC963FFD47E93FA8D1C3B151D" authority="Kupriyanova, 1993 b" authorityName="Kupriyanova" authorityYear="1993" box="[151,626,1365,1391]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Bathyditrupa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hovei">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC963FFD47E93FA8D1F31151C" box="[151,376,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Bathyditrupa hovei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF854B1FC963FFD47F7BFA8D1C3B151D" author="Kupriyanova, E. K." box="[383,626,1365,1391]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="21 - 28" refId="ref62782" refString="Kupriyanova, E. K. (1993 b) Deep-water Serpulidae (Annelida, Polychaeta) from the Kurile-Kamchatka trench: 2. Genera Bathyditrupa, Bathyvermilia and Protis. Zoologichesky Zhurnal, 72, 21 - 28." type="journal article" year="1993">Kupriyanova, 1993b</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, Kurile-Kamchatka trench and North Pacific Ocean; abyssal.
</paragraph>
